org.regenstrief.ucum
Class UnitSystem

java.lang.Object
  org.regenstrief.ucum.UnitSystem
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.xml.sax.ContentHandler
public final class UnitSystem
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.xml.sax.ContentHandler

Loads the Unit definitions from an XML document accessed from a certain URL. This class is a singleton whose object at this time acts as a ContentHandler. The static method loadUnits is called from some static context and causes the units definition to be parsed and the units created. FIXME: this is too much static stuff. I should probably call the UnitLoader a "UnitSystem", not have it be a singleton, but have it contain all those static data structures like the dimension definitions, the prefix map, and the unit maps. I don't really want to suggest that there should ever be multiple unit systems used at the same time.
